                @* <p>The automotive world is witnessing a dramatic shift, driven by the dual forces of electrification and high-octane motorsport excitement. Bridging these two dynamic worlds is a feat few manufacturers can claim, but the Indian automotive giant Mahindra has emphatically stepped forward to redefine the equation. Introducing the highly-anticipated <span class="font-weight-700">Mahindra BE 6 Formula E Edition,</span> the company has rolled out what is proudly proclaimed as the world’s first Formula E-themed special edition SUV. This remarkable electric vehicle (EV) is far more than just a cosmetic upgrade; it is a profound celebration of Mahindra’s deep-rooted and successful involvement in the ABB FIA Formula E World Championship.</p> *@
                <p>For those who follow the electric motorsport scene, Mahindra Racing has become synonymous with innovation and competitive spirit, being the only Indian team to claim victory on the Formula E grid. This special edition BE 6 captures that pedigree and channels the racing team's technological prowess and design intensity directly into a street-legal machine. The BE 6 is part of Mahindra’s Born Electric (BE) range, built upon the revolutionary INGLO platform, marking the company's "Scream Electric" philosophy. This edition doesn't just whisper 'electric'; it shouts 'performance' with every meticulously crafted detail.</p>
                <p>The launch of the BE 6 Formula E Edition is a defining moment, particularly for the burgeoning youth audience in India who view racing not just as a sport, but as a lifestyle statement. As R Velusamy, President - Automotive Business, Mahindra & Mahindra Ltd., highlighted, this vehicle was "built by listening to that energy," translating a cultural shift into a machine that is bold, emotional, and proudly made in India. It is designed to be the perfect conduit for the energy, thrill, and uncompromised style of electric racing, making it a must-have for the discerning enthusiast browsing sites like <span class="font-weight-700">BikeCarHub </span>for the latest and greatest in the EV segment.</p>
                <h3 class="subheading">Design Philosophy: The Race-to-Road Aesthetic</h3>
                <div class="row m-b20">
                    <div class="col-lg-12 col-md-12 text-center image-height"><img src="~/images/blogs/2025/nov/mahindra be/left.webp" alt="left" title="left" loading="lazy" /></div>
                </div>
                <p>The design language of the BE 6 Formula E Edition is a masterclass in aggressive, aerodynamic styling, expertly integrating motorsport cues without sacrificing everyday functionality. The mandate given to the design team was clear: infuse every element with 'motorsport intensity.' The result is a vehicle that looks like it belongs both on the grid and gliding silently through city streets.</p>
                <p><span class="font-weight-700">A. Exterior: Aerodynamics, Decals, and the Iconic Orange Accent</span></p>
                <p>The special edition immediately differentiates itself from the standard BE 6 with a suite of race-inspired modifications. The front fascia undergoes a dramatic transformation, moving towards a more aggressive stance. Notably, the BE 6 Formula E Edition features distinctive <span class="font-weight-700">circular LED projector headlamps, </span>a striking change from the standard version, giving it a unique, focused look.</p>
                <p>The bumpers, both front and rear, have been significantly reworked. The front bumper is sculpted for superior airflow, while the rear features a new, faux skid plate finished in brushed aluminium, replacing some of the standard model’s diffuser elements with a cleaner, yet pronounced aesthetic. Aerodynamics play a key role, highlighted by the addition of an <span class="font-weight-700">aero wing </span>and a secondary<span class="font-weight-700"> integrated spoiler </span>on the boot lid, elements designed to manage and break airflow effectively, increasing stability at higher speeds—a true nod to its racing heritage.</p>
                <p>The commitment to the Formula E theme is most visible in the details:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Colour Palette: </span>Available in four distinctive colours—Firestorm Orange, Tango Red, Everest White, and Stealth Black—each shade accentuates the vehicle's dynamic lines.</li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Formula E Graphics: </span>The bodywork is adorned with bespoke, race-themed graphics and decals on the doors, fenders, and bonnet, making its racing DNA unmistakable.</li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Orange Accents:</span> Signature orange highlights—the official colour of Mahindra Racing—are strategically placed on the front grille elements, the orange tow hook, and the<span class="font-weight-700"> red brake calipers </span>visible through the wheels, adding a performance-focused visual flair.</li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Wheels:</span> The SUV sits proudly on specially designed <span class="font-weight-700">20-inch alloy wheels</span> with a dark-tinted finish, featuring an aero-focused design inspired by the 2023 Rall-E concept car, further underscoring its performance credentials.</li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Lighting: </span>The rear features a sleek, sophisticated LED lightbar connecting the taillights, ensuring a high-tech and premium appearance.</li>
                </ul>
                <p><span class="font-weight-700">B. Interior: Cockpit-Inspired Luxury and Racing Spirit</span></p>
                <p>Step inside the BE 6 Formula E Edition, and the cabin echoes the exterior’s performance narrative while wrapping occupants in luxurious, cutting-edge technology. The standard BE 6 interior is carried over but elevated with subtle yet impactful Formula E-specific detailing.</p>
                <p>The key aesthetic changes include:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Carbon-Fibre Finishes:</span> The dashboard and door trims receive a premium, high-performance touch with carbon-fibre finished elements, providing a tactile sense of motorsport-grade quality.</li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Formula E Branding: </span>Exclusive Formula E badging and unique orange stitching are found on the seats and seat belts, continuously reminding the driver and passengers of the vehicle's special status.</li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Celebratory Plaque:</span> A unique celebratory plaque is fixed on the centre console, confirming the vehicle's limited-edition nature and connection to Mahindra Racing.</li>
