                <h3 class="subheading">The INGLO Platform: Foundation of the Electric Future</h3>
                <div class="row m-b20">
                    <div class="col-lg-12 col-md-12 text-center image-height"><img src="~/images/blogs/2025/nov/mahindra be/red.webp" alt="red" title="red" loading="lazy" /></div>
                </div>

                <p>At the heart of the Mahindra BE 6 Formula E Edition lies the revolutionary <span class="font-weight-700">INGLO (INdia Global) </span>electric origin architecture. This dedicated EV skateboard platform is the backbone of Mahindra’s entire Born Electric range and is crucial to the BE 6’s packaging, performance, and impressive range capabilities.</p>
                <p>The INGLO platform is a modular, flexible chassis engineered purely for electrification, allowing for better weight distribution, a lower centre of gravity, and maximized interior space—a key advantage over conventional cars adapted for EV use. The 3-in-1 integrated powertrain is optimized for this architecture, providing efficiency and power delivery that can truly rival global benchmarks.</p>
                <p>The structural integrity of the platform is also a major highlight, engineered to incorporate a robust battery protection frame and safety features that secure the LFP (Lithium Iron Phosphate) battery pack. This grounds-up approach ensures that the BE 6 is not just fast, but fundamentally safe and stable. The high-power steering with Variable Gear Ratio (VGR) built into the INGLO architecture allows for an impressively tight turning circle (10m TCD), making the 4,371mm long SUV surprisingly nimble for its size in city environments.</p>
                <h3 class="subheading">Power and Performance: An Electrifying Thrill</h3>
                <div class="row m-b20">
                    <div class="col-lg-12 col-md-12 text-center image-height"><img src="~/images/blogs/2025/nov/mahindra be/side.webp" alt="side" title="side" loading="lazy" /></div>
                </div>

                <p>The essence of the Formula E Edition is performance, and Mahindra has ensured that the BE 6 lives up to its race-inspired identity. Unlike the standard BE 6, which offers multiple battery and power options, the Formula E Edition is exclusively powered by the larger, high-performance <span class="font-weight-700">79 kWh battery pack.</span></p>
                <p><span class="font-weight-700">A. Motor and Torque Delivery</span></p>
                <p>The electric motor setup is a potent, rear-mounted Permanent Magnet Synchronous Motor (PMSM), driving the rear wheels (RWD).</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Maximum Power: </span>282 bhp (or 285 PS / 210 kW)</li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Peak Torque:</span> 380 Nm</li>
                </ul>
                <p>This configuration delivers instantaneous and thrilling acceleration. The claimed <span class="font-weight-700">0-100 km/h sprint is dispatched in a swift 6.7 seconds, </span>firmly placing the BE 6 Formula E Edition in the league of performance SUVs. The top speed is a respectable 202 km/h. Furthermore, the edition features <span class="font-weight-700">Race-mode-inspired torque delivery,</span> ensuring that the driver feels a sharper, more immediate response from the throttle, mirroring the aggressive power delivery expected in a competitive racing environment. The driving modes and multi-step regeneration, controllable via paddle shifters, allow the driver to fine-tune the performance characteristics to suit their mood or the driving conditions.</p>
                <p><span class="font-weight-700">B. Advanced Dynamics and Braking</span></p>
                <p>Performance is incomplete without control. The BE 6 Formula E Edition, particularly the top-spec FE3 variant, takes this aspect seriously by offering<span class="font-weight-700"> adaptive suspension. </span>This advanced technology allows the suspension damping characteristics to be continuously adjusted in real-time based on road conditions, speed, and driving input. This translates to an unparalleled combination of a firm, planted feel during aggressive cornering and a plush, comfortable ride on poor road surfaces—a distinct advantage over its rivals.</p>
                <p>Complementing the power is the sophisticated <span class="font-weight-700">Brake-by-wire technology </span>with an Integrated Electronic Booster (IEB), ensuring precise, consistent, and powerful stopping force. All four wheels are fitted with disc brakes, providing confidence-inspiring control even when attempting high-speed maneuvers.</p>
                <h3 class="subheading">Range and Efficiency: Going the Distance</h3>
                <div class="row m-b20">
                    <div class="col-lg-12 col-md-12 text-center image-height"><img src="~/images/blogs/2025/nov/mahindra be/black.webp" alt="black" title="black" loading="lazy" /></div>
                </div>

                <p>While performance is paramount for a special edition, an electric vehicle’s true measure of success in the mainstream market, as often discussed on platforms like <span class="font-weight-700">BikeCarHub, </span>is its range and charging capability. The Mahindra BE 6 Formula E Edition excels here, leveraging the full potential of its 79 kWh battery.</p>
                <p><span class="font-weight-700">A. Impressive Range Figures</span></p>
                <p>The BE 6 Formula E Edition boasts a certified range (MIDC P1+P2 combined) of an outstanding <span class="font-weight-700">682 km to 683 km </span>on a single charge. While standardized testing cycles often yield higher numbers, Mahindra has also provided a more realistic claimed<span class="font-weight-700"> real-world range of 500 km. </span>This figure is highly competitive and effectively eliminates range anxiety for daily commutes and even intercity travel, positioning the BE 6 as a leader in its segment for practical, long-distance electric mobility.</p>
                <p><span class="font-weight-700">B. Charging Technology: Back on Track Quickly</span></p>
