                <h3 class="subheading">Safety and Assistance Systems</h3>
                <p>Safety is non-negotiable, and the BE 6 Formula E Edition is equipped with a comprehensive safety arsenal, built on the robust INGLO platform's foundation.</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Passive Safety:</span> The SUV is protected by<span class="font-weight-700"> six airbags</span> (Driver, Front Passenger, 2 Curtain, Driver Side, Front Passenger Side) as standard, along with disc brakes on all four wheels, ABS with EBD, and electronic stability control (ESP).</li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Driver Assistance:</span> Key driver assistance features include a<span class="font-weight-700"> 360-degree camera</span> with a Blind Spot Monitor, a Tyre Pressure Monitoring System (TPMS), and Driver Drowsiness Detection.</li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">ADAS Context: </span>A crucial point for prospective buyers on <span class="font-weight-700">BikeCarHub</span> to note is the variant-specific feature distribution. While the standard BE 6 offers Level 2 ADAS on certain high-end trims, the <span class="font-weight-700">FE2 variant of the Formula E Edition prioritizes features like the 360-degree camera and front parking sensors over the full ADAS suite.</span> The ADAS features (such as Adaptive Cruise Control and Lane Keep Assist) are often considered vital, so buyers must weigh their priorities between the race-themed aesthetics/exclusivity package and the ADAS capability. The optional FE3 trim primarily focuses on enhanced dynamics via the adaptive suspension.</li>
